.TH START\-HYPRLAND 1 "2025-12-17" "hyprland 0.53.3" "Hyprland Ecosystem"
.SH NAME
start\-hyprland \- start the Hyprland compositor with a watchdog process
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B start\-hyprland
.RI [ options ]
.RB [ \-\- " " \fIhyprland\-args\fR... ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B start\-hyprland
is a wrapper that launches the Hyprland compositor through a watchdog
process.
If Hyprland exits uncleanly, the watchdog restarts it in safe mode.
The process terminates only when Hyprland exits normally.
.PP
This is the recommended method for starting Hyprland from a display manager
or TTY.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help information.
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-path " " \fIpath\fR
Override the path to the Hyprland executable.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-nixgl
Force disable nixGL usage.
.TP
.B \-\-
All arguments after this separator are passed directly to the Hyprland
executable.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR Hyprland (1),
.BR hyprctl (1)
.SH AUTHOR
The Hyprland Development Team
